  => "  recover_lb(r) = 1 - 4/r (c=4 task-agnostic prior)"
  => "  predicted Pareto product (save·recover): r=8 → 0.983·0.5 = 0.492;"
  => "    r=12 → 0.974·0.667 = 0.649 (theoretically dominant on this prior)"
  => "  Honest note from source: 'task-specific c may make r=8 best at GPU train'"
  => "Anchors: r=4=τ EXACT, r=6=n EXACT, r=8=σ-τ EXACT, r=12=σ EXACT, r=16=2^τ EXACT"
  => "Status: dry-run PASS — GLUE/SuperGLUE GPU bench pending (orig 603-line Py preserved)"
  |> ~/core/n6-architecture/experiments/ai-efficiency/experiment_lora_r8_optimality.hexa

